Ngeneric:Invisible-Pin|pin@113||-163|-160.5|||||SIM_spice_card(D5G1;)S[* --- Neuromorphic Full Adder Testbench ---,* 1. Supply Voltage,vdd vdd 0 DC 1.8,* 2. Analog Bias Reference Voltages,* We define parameters for both biases so you can easily tune them.,* V_COUT_BIAS controls the threshold for the Carry-Out neuron.,* V_SUM_BIAS controls the threshold for the Sum neuron.,.param V_COUT_BIAS = 1.4,.param V_SUM_BIAS = 0.8,vCoutBias coutbias 0 DC {V_COUT_BIAS},vSumBias sumbias 0 DC {V_SUM_BIAS},"* Optional: If you want to sweep one of the biases to find the sweet spot, ",* uncomment ONE of the following lines. (Do not sweep both at the same time).,* .step param V_COUT_BIAS 0.5 1.5 0.1,* .step param V_SUM_BIAS 0.5 1.5 0.1,* 3. Input Stimulus (Testing all 8 states: 000 to 111),* Cin toggles fastest (Period = 20ns),vCin cin 0 PULSE (0 1.8 0 0.1n 0.1n 10n 20n),* B toggles half as fast as Cin (Period = 40ns),vB B 0 PULSE (0 1.8 0 0.1n 0.1n 20n 40n),* A toggles half as fast as B (Period = 80ns),vA A 0 PULSE (0 1.8 0 0.1n 0.1n 40n 80n),* 4. Output Load Capacitance,cf_cout Cout 0 200fF,cf_sum Sum 0 200fF,* 5. Analysis,* Run transient analysis for 90ns to comfortably capture the full 80ns cycle,.tran 0.1n 90n,* 6. Library Include,".include \"C:\\Users\\enslenc1\\Documents\\GitHub\\VLSI\\ElectricVLSI\\TransistorSpecs\\tsmc018.lib\""]
