Ngeneric:Invisible-Pin|pin@20||-88|-73.5|||||SIM_spice_card(D5G1;)S[* --- Neuromorphic NAND Gate Testbench ---,* 1. Supply Voltage,* Note: TSMC 0.18um typically uses a 1.8V core voltage. If your layout ,"* uses 3.3V thick-oxide I/O devices, change this 1.8 to 3.0 or 3.3.",vdd vdd 0 DC 1.8,* 2. Analog Bias Reference Voltage (V_REF),"* Instead of a static DC voltage, we define a parameter to sweep the bias.",* This will simulate how tuning V_REF changes the neuron's logic threshold.,.param VBIAS = 0.8,vRef vRef 0 DC {VBIAS},* Sweep VBIAS from 0.5V to 1.5V in 0.1V increments to find the exact NAND threshold,.step param VBIAS 0.5 1.5 0.1,* 3. Input Stimulus (Testing the Truth Table),* Pulse format: (V_initial V_peak T_delay T_rise T_fall Pulse_Width Period),* Input A pulses every 20ns,vA A 0 PULSE (0 1.8 0 0.1n 0.1n 10n 20n),* Input B pulses every 40ns. ,"* Combined with A, this tests states: 00 (0-10ns), 10 (10-20ns), 01 (20-30ns), 11 (30-40ns)",vB B 0 PULSE (0 1.8 0 0.1n 0.1n 20n 40n),* 4. Output Load Capacitance,* Simulates parasitic routing or oscilloscope probe capacitance,cf V_OUT 0 200fF,* 5. Analysis,* Run transient analysis for 50ns to capture a full cycle of all four states,.tran 0.1n 50n,* 6. Library Include,".include \"C:\\Users\\enslenc1\\Documents\\GitHub\\VLSI\\ElectricVLSI\\TransistorSpecs\\tsmc018.lib\""]
